The paper deals with a communication problem in which input bits are broadcasted among processors and corrupted with some probability. This falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and distributed computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. The paper also involves algorithms for computation, which can be categorized under the data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the probability of success for the algorithms, which can be considered under the statistical learning (cs.SI) sub-category.
